            Money used to purchase an annuity will  be locked into a contract. You should use no more than 50% of your retirement  assets (excluding your home) and keep  at least $20,000 on hand for emergencies.
        

























Important Annuity Benefits

Purchase this fixed immediate annuity with funds from savings and CDs, or 401(k)s and IRAs.1
Receive fixed monthly income payments regardless of what's happening in the economy.
Guaranteed income no matter how long you live.
Your money won't be lost if you pass away prematurely.2
Exclusively for AARP members.


