1-800-313-6841.


8 a.m. to 6 p.m. (ET) Monday - Friday or 9 a.m. to 5 p.m. Saturday.


Backed by the financial strength of New York Life Insurance and Annuity Corporation — Program endorsed by AARP






Available to members ages 50 – 89 and spouses ages 45 – 89.
 
1 Your FREE information kit will provide more details, including limitations, exclusions and important guidelines. 
2 With a built-in cash refund feature, if you die before your payments equal your annuity purchase price, your beneficiary will be paid the difference.


New York Life Insurance and Annuity Corporation pays royalty fees to AARP for the use of its intellectual property. These fees are used for the general purposes of AARP. AARP and its affiliates are not insurers. New York Life Insurance and Annuity Corporation is a wholly owned subsidiary of New York Life Insurance Company. AARP does not employ or endorse agents, producers or brokers.
Complete terms and conditions are set forth in the group policy issued by New York Life Insurance and Annuity Corporation to the Trustee of the AARP Annuity Trust.
The AARP Lifetime Income Program is underwritten by New York Life Insurance and Annuity Corporation (NYLIAC), a Delaware Corporation, Newark, DE 19713. AARP membership is required for Program eligibility. Guarantees are based on the claims-paying ability of NYLIAC. Specific products and features not available in all states or countries. (Group policy forms IA-02 and IA-04.)
